In the Season 3 opener, Vincent considers proposing to Catherine. But when she discovers a case, everything goes out the window.

Season 2 of this supernatural crime drama begins with a changed Vincent (Jay Ryan) carrying out a mysterious mission. Later, Cat (Kristin Kreuk) learns about her past at her high-school reunion, J.T. (Austin Basis) gets kidnapped, and an unexpected alliance is formed with the FBI. Nina Lisandrello and Sendhil Ramamurthy also return for the second season.

An unlikely romance blooms between a homicide detective and a man with supernatural powers in the first series of this drama. While investigating a murder case, Cat (Kristin Kreuk) stumbles upon the trail of Vincent (Jay Ryan), a mysterious ex-soldier who was thought to be dead. As the two get to know each other, Cat discovers that Vincent holds clues about her mother's death. Meanwhile, Cat must help Vincent avoid capture by the dangerous company that was responsible for his mutant transformation. Other series regulars in Series 1 include Nina Lisandrello, Max Brown, Brian White and Austin Basis.

A cult fantasy about a lawyer who befriends---and eventually falls for---a kindly man-beast who lives in a subterranean world beneath New York City. Strange, moody and oddly romantic, the series had unusually loyal fans, but, alas, not enough of them and was gone within three years.

Season 12 of this comedy show centers around the wild adventures of the gang responsible for the notorious Paddy's Pub. Story lines this season include the gang going to a water park; Frank (Danny Danny DeVito) dealing with a public relations scandal; and Dennis having to actually make a real-life decision that could change the whole dynamic of the group. Guest stars include Scott Bakula, Dana White and Lynne Marie Stewart.

Season 11 of this comedy show continues to follow the mishaps and insane experiences of the gang behind the notorious Paddy's Pub. This season, story lines include the gang playing another game of Chardee MacDennis; Mac (Rob McElhenney) and Dennis (Glenn Howerton) trying to live in the suburbs; and the whole gang going on a Christian-theme cruise. Guest stars include Reginald VelJohnson, Brian Doyle-Murray and Guillermo del Toro.

Season 10 of this comedy series continues to follow the misadventures of Mac (Rob McElhenney), Dennis (Glenn Howerton), Charlie (Charlie Day), Dee (Kaitlin Olson) and Frank (Danny DeVito), all whom work at the infamous Paddy's Pub. This season, the gang tackle challenges like trying to beat Wade Boggs' record of drinking 70 beers on a cross-country flight, attempting to navigate the world of online dating, and participating in a famous TV game show. Guest stars this season include Wade Boggs, Dax Shepard and Keegan-Michael Key.

Dee (Kaitlin Olson) tries her hand at stand-up comedy as the crew from Paddy's Pub return for Series 9. Later, gun ownership is debated, Mac (Rob McElhenney) gets a special day devoted to him, and Charlie (Charlie Day) quits his job at the bar. Seann William Scott makes an appearance along the way, while Danny DeVito and Glenn Howerton are back as Frank and Dennis.

The Paddy's Pub gang return for an eighth series of ill-conceived misadventures featuring a crashed wedding, a painting by Adolf Hitler and a makeshift legal trial over spilled milk. Dennis (Glenn Howerton) and his sister Dee (Kaitlin Olson) first must decide the fate of their ailing grandfather, who happens to be a former Nazi. Later, their father Frank (Danny DeVito) masterminds a get-rich-quick scheme involving the city's trash, and Mac (Rob McElhenney) helps Charlie (Charlie Day) plan a sham fund-raiser. The gang also uncharacteristically seek an outside opinion during a visit to a therapist's office, but, as expected, more problems than solutions arise.

Frank (Danny DeVito) wants to marry a prostitute as the crew return for Series 7. Later, Dennis (Glenn Howerton) and Charlie (Charlie Day) track down an annoying Paddy's patron, and Dee (Kaitlin Olson) tries to weasel her way out of an IRS audit. Also, Mac (Rob McElhenney) gets fat.

Mac (Rob McElhenney) defends traditional marriage as the gang return for a sixth series. Elsewhere, Charlie (Charlie Day) hunts rats in Paddy's basement, and Dee (Kaitlin Olson) takes a job as a substitute teacher. Danny DeVito and Glenn Howerton are also back as Frank and Dennis.

The gang are back for Series 5 as Frank (Danny DeVito), Mac (Rob McElhenney) and Dennis (Glenn Howerton) try their hand at real estate. Meanwhile, Charlie (Charlie Day) squares off with a lawyer over the intricacies of the judicial system, and Dee (Kaitlin Olson) arranges to be a surrogate mother for a rich couple.

The slacker crew from Paddy's Pub return for a fourth series of hilarious high jinks. Mac (Rob McElhenney), Dennis (Glenn Howerton) and Charlie (Charlie Day) try selling gasoline door-to-door, while Dee (Kaitlin Olson) suffers a heart attack. Danny DeVito is also back as Frank.

The amoral shenanigans of the slacker, pub-owning gang are kicked up a notch in Series 3 as Mac (Rob McElhenney) is suspected of being a serial killer, Dennis (Glenn Howerton) is mistaken for a child molester, and Dee (Kaitlin Olson) and Mac try to make a buck off a baby they find in a dumpster. The gang even gets mixed up with the mob and the only way out is for Dennis to become a male escort. Maybe such outlandish behaviour is simply in their genes. After all, Frank (Danny DeVito), the father of Dee and Dennis, is totally out of control and has a "gang" of his own, the Yellow Jacket Boys (played by the doo-wop group the Mighty Echoes). And the dear old dad of Mac is no better. He's an ex-con and has his eye on Dee, who's definitely not interested. She dates a mentally challenged rapper instead. Dee also tries out for the professional football team, the Philadelphia Eagles, as does Mac, Dennis and Doyle McPoyle (Bob Rusch), reigniting the gang's feud with the inbred Doyle and his equally creepy brothers Liam and Ryan (Jimmi Simpson and Nate Mooney). Later on, the McPoyles invade Paddy's and it escalates into a hostage situation. The seriescloses with Charlie (Charlie Day) inadvertently putting the bar up as the grand prize in a dance marathon.

Danny DeVito joins the cast as the rest of the gang return for a second series of outrageous misadventures. Dennis (Glenn Howerton) runs for office at one point, and Frank (DeVito) puts Charlie (Charlie Day) in charge of the bar. Other familiar faces in Series 2 include Rob McElhenney and Kaitlin Olson.

The first series of "It's Always Sunny in Philadelphia" follows four dissolute friends as they attempt to run a struggling pub. Along the way, Charlie (Charlie Day) fears he may have cancer, and Mac (Rob McElhenney) gets involved with a transvestite. Glenn Howerton and Kaitlin Olson also star.
